  <static seed="732" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring71.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{10x^{2}+14x+14}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>2\mathopen{}\left(5x^{2}+7x+7\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>2</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{10x^{2}+14x+14}={2\mathopen{}\left(5x^{2}+7x+7\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
